title.narrative: INCLUSIVE EDUCATION

description.narrative: Parents, teachers, communities and other partners have increased capacity to actively support inclusive quality education and children and adolescents have equitable access to inclusive and quality learning opportunities., which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Access To Quality Learning Opportunities (Covid), Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement (Covid), Operations Support To Programme Delivery. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, children, especially the most disadvantaged, will acquire knowledge and skills in an inclusive, safe, quality learning environment to complete pre-primary, primary, transit to secondary and complete lower secondary education

title.narrative: Parents, teachers, communities and other partners have increased capacity to actively support inclusive quality education andchildren and adolescents have equitable access to inclusive and quality learning opportunities.

description.narrative: Due to the military takeover and ongoing COVID 19 pandemic in Myanmar, programming under this output has moved from a focus on systems strengthening to a focus on community based programming to support learning for the most disadvantaged through an open learning strategy for expansion of access to materials and support. In 2021, UNICEF reached 66,119 primary and middle school aged children (female: 33,015) and 2,059 teachers (female: 762), including community volunteer teachers to support continuity of learning. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:14/01/2022
